<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idbf615129-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s12133"><num value="12133">§ 12133.</num><heading> Enforcement</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The remedies, procedures, and rights set forth in <ref href="/us/usc/t29/s794a">section 794a of title 29</ref> shall be the remedies, procedures, and rights this subchapter provides to any person alleging discrimination on the basis of disability in violation of <ref href="/us/usc/t42/s12132">section 12132 of this title</ref>.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idbf61512a-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa">(<ref href="/us/pl/101/336/tII/s203">Pub. L. 101–336, title II, § 203</ref>, <date date="1990-07-26">July 26, 1990</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/104/337">104 Stat. 337</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idbf61512b-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="statutoryNotes" id="idbf61512c-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"><heading class="centered"><b>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="effectiveDate" id="idbf61512d-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Effective Date</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section effective 18 months after <date date="1990-07-26">July 26, 1990</date>, see <ref href="/us/pl/101/336/s205/a">section 205(a) of Pub. L. 101–336</ref>, set out as a note under <ref href="/us/usc/t42/s12131">section 12131 of this title</ref>.</p>
</note>
</notes>
</section>
